# TechNinja Machine JSON Template

**File name:** `_TEMPLATE.machine.json`

This file is the **canonical starting point** for adding any new machine to TechNinja.

Do **not** copy an existing machine file as a base. Always start from this template.

---

## Template

```json
{
  "schemaVersion": "1.0",

  "machine": "Machine display name (shown to technicians)",

  "meta": {
    "manufacturer": "",
    "model": "",
    "introducedBy": "",
    "lastUpdated": "",
    "notes": ""
  },

  "symptoms": [
    {
      "id": "example_symptom_id",
      "name": "What the technician is experiencing",
      "description": "Optional clarifying detail",
      "start": "step_start"
    }
  ],

  "steps": {
    "step_start": {
      "text": "First diagnostic question or action",
      "note": "Optional technician hint or context",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Yes / condition met",
          "next": "step_followup",
          "primary": true
        },
        {
          "label": "No / condition not met",
          "next": "result_unknown"
        }
      ]
    },

    "step_followup": {
      "text": "Follow-up diagnostic step",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Confirmed",
          "next": "result_confirmed"
        },
        {
          "label": "Not confirmed",
          "next": "result_unknown"
        }
      ]
    },

    "result_confirmed": {
      "text": "Fault identified",
      "result": {
        "title": "Confirmed fault name",
        "likelyCause": "Short explanation of why this fault occurs",
        "fieldFix": [
          "Practical field fix steps",
          "Things a technician can realistically do onsite"
        ],
        "official": [
          "OEM-recommended fix or service manual reference"
        ],
        "warnings": [
          "Safety, warranty, or repeat-visit warnings"
        ],
        "confidence": "medium",
        "provenance": "field-confirmed"
      }
    },

    "result_unknown": {
      "text": "Unable to confirm fault",
      "result": {
        "title": "Unconfirmed fault",
        "likelyCause": "Insufficient or conflicting data",
        "fieldFix": [],
        "official": [],
        "warnings": [],
        "confidence": "low",
        "provenance": "anecdotal"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Required conventions

### IDs

* All `id` and `step_*` values are **stable identifiers**
* Never rename IDs once published
* Use lowercase, underscores, no spaces

### Navigation

* Every `next` value **must exist** as a step key
* Terminal steps are detected **only** by the presence of `result`

### Confidence & provenance

Allowed values:

* `confidence`: `low`, `medium`, `high`
* `provenance`: `manual`, `field-confirmed`, `anecdotal`

Rules:

* `high` confidence requires `manual` or `field-confirmed`
* Absence of these fields implies **unknown**, not high confidence

---

## Intent

This template prioritises:

* Field usability
* Explicit uncertainty
* Survivability under handover

If you are unsure, choose **lower confidence** and document uncertainty.
